Client: DTE Energy, Detroit MI
Nov 2016- Oct2017
Role: Sr. UI/UX developer & designer
Responsibilities:
- Introduced application wide consistency layouts, design patterns, style guides and wireframe.
- Established UX/CX design as the first stage of all Web and mobile application developments, instituting a user centered design (UCD) approach.
- Human centered UX Designer who delivers repeated success using research, communication, content strategy, information architecture, visual design, development & usability testing.
- Designing websites/landing page for clients using Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, and Axure RP8
- Adobe Creative Suite Instructor(After Effort).
- Worked on Adobe Experience Manager - Mobile Product. Extended customer on demand portal capabilities and developing scalable backend web services to support various product capabilities
- Created internal portal using wireframe and prototypes.
- Develop detailed storyboards, wireframes, concepts, mockups, and interactive prototypes
- E­commerce site built usingHTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript.
- Developed by using Node.js, React JS.
- Developed a core component of Analytics with knockout Js.
- Implemented MVVM in all interactive views using jQuery and Knockout.js
- Designed, Developed React native Android and IOS.
- Utilize Ionics’s Components, Pages, Providers, Services and Directive for application development.
- Tested DTE energy application on Mobile Devices like IOS, Android, and Blackberry for DTE energy mobile app
- Establishing the information architecture, delivering functional requirements analysis, wireframes, design mock­ups and front­end design development guidelines.
- Utilized JavaScript for rich user interactions for company prototype.
- Developed applications VoIP alone both android and iOS platform, my cross-platform development skills mastered by developing VoIP.
- Designed and developed advanced applications for the Android platform
- Developed React JS pages, Web services calls and AJAX calls for the application.
- Used React JS in development of the web application to bind the data/model that is being retrieved from a database through services provided in a controller to the view using scope.
- Worked on Front end by using JavaScript.
- Managed tools like Subversion, JIRA and Performed maintenance and troubleshooting of build/ deployment systems.
- Administration and configuration management of version control systems GIT.
Environment: HTML, XML, CSS3, JavaScript, REST API, Adobe Experience Manager, wireframes, prototypes Angular.js 2, React Native, JQuery, Eclipse, React.JS AJAX, JSON, JDBC, Bootstrap, Ionics’s, Cordova, Jenkins, Jira, SQL Server 12-16, Maven and Windows XP, Visio, GIT, OmniGraffle etc….
